 *1325503248*Page breaks using raw directives in Sphinx
 When I use Sphinx to write a book manuscript, for example, I have a need to have page breaks before section headings. In my case, I print out the HTML and take it with me only when I go out to review it, so by embedding a tag with the page-break-after: always style in the raw directive where I want the page break, I can make a page break at the page break is now performed at the specified position when printed as expected.
 
 >||
 .. raw:: html
 
    <p style="page-break-after: always" />
 ||<
 
 Although I achieved my goal for the time being, I don't like to have such a thing buried in the manuscript (and it would give me a shock when I hand it to an editor who is not familiar with reST), so it would be nice if Sphinx could add "style="page-break-before: always" to all h2 tags except the first one. I wish I could add "style="page-break-before: always" to h2 tags except for the first time" or something like that.
 
