 *1325516319*Tempur triangle cushion experience
 My wife gave me a Tempur triangle seat cushion (<a href="http://www.amazon.co.jp/gp/product/B0019M1JOO/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=nishiohirokaz-22& linkCode=as2&camp=247&creative=7399&creativeASIN=B0019M1JOO">Tempur(R) PC seat cushion</a>) for me and I use it happily.
 
 This is what it looks like at my desk at work.
 
 f:id:nishiohirokazu:20111228173040j:image
 
 At home, I mix it between sitting on the floor and pulling it on the floor as I see fit. This is because I have a hot carpet underneath and sometimes I want to warm up.
 
 f:id:nishiohirokazu:20120102235600j:image
 
 
 My chair at work is an Aeron chair for backward leaning posture and my chair at home is a Varier Balans(<a href='https://www.google.com/search?q=varier+balans&hl=en&safe=off&prmd=imvns&source= lnms&tbm=isch&ei=I8gBT-i-NcXWmAX-qPC2DQ&sa=X&oi=mode_link&ct=mode&cd=2&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAQ&biw=1189&BIH=579'>image search</a>) without a backrest. I'm a forward leaner, so I had a bit of a posture mismatch and felt tired on the backs of my knees and calves. I was wondering if pulling out this cushion would improve it a lot. I've only used it for one day at work, so I'm not sure about the compatibility with the Aeron chair, but when I use it at home when I work on the hot carpet, it seems to put less stress on my lower back because my pelvis stands up compared to sitting directly on the floor.
